Houlihan Lokey, Inc. Class A (NYSE:HLI) Closed 8.0% Above Its 50 Day Average - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Houlihan Lokey, Inc. Class A (NYSE:HLI) Closed 8.0% Above Its 50 Day Average
July 14, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Shares are trading at $36.99 marginally over the 50 day moving average of $34.24 and slightly over the 200 day moving average of $32.72.  The 50 day moving average went up $2.75 or +8.03% and the 200 day average went up $4.27 or +13.04%.  (NYSE:HLI) shares saw heavy trading volume with 163K shares changing hands by the end of trading on Friday.  Overall, volume was up 20.95% over the stocks normal daily volume. 
 These firms have also modified their investment in HLI.   Clinton Group Inc bolstered its holdings by buying 20,095 shares an increase of 128.5% from 12/31/2016 to 03/31/2017. Clinton Group Inc claims 35,734 shares with a value of $1,231,000. The total value of its holdings increased 152.8%. Mackenzie Financial Corp trimmed its ownership by shedding 12,300 shares a decrease of 54.2%. Mackenzie Financial Corp currently owns 10,400 shares valued at $358,000. The value of the position overall is down by 49.3%.
 As of quarter end Morgan Stanley had disposed of  a total of 1,212 shares trimming its position 80.2%. The value of the total investment in Houlihan Lokey, Inc. Class A decreased from $47,000 to $10,000 a change of 78.7% since the last quarter. Tower Research Capital LLC (trc) expanded its investment by buying 1,645 shares an increase of 579.2% as of 03/31/2017. Tower Research Capital LLC (trc) controls 1,929 shares worth $66,000. The total value of its holdings increased 1,000.0%.





  On August 18 the stock rating was downgraded to “Hold” from “Buy” by Sandler O'Neill. On September 8 analysts at Sandler O’Neill added the stock to its research portfolio with a rating of “Buy” and a price target of $25.00.
 On September 8, 2015 Goldman Sachs issued its first research report on the stock with an initial rating of “Neutral” and establishing a price target of $25.00.
 The company is now up since yesterday’s close of $36.77.  Houlihan Lokey, Inc. Class A declared a dividend for shareholders paid on Thursday the 15th of June 2017.  The dividend payment was $0.200 per share for the quarter or $0.80 on an annualized basis.  This dividend represents a yeild of $2.18 which is the dividend as a percentage of the current share price.  The ex-dividend date was set for Wednesday the 31st of May 2017. 
 Houlihan Lokey, Inc. Class A’s P/E ratio is 22.69 and market cap is 2.48B.  In the latest earnings report the EPS was $1.63 and is expected to be $1.95 for the current year with 67,128,000 shares outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is expected be $0.41 with next year’s EPS anticipated to be $2.09. 
 Houlihan Lokey, Inc., launched on June 1, 2015, is a global independent investment bank that focuses on mergers and acquisitions (M&A), financings, financial restructurings and financial advisory services. The Company operates through three segments: Corporate Finance, Financial Restructuring and Financial Advisory Services. The Company, through its offices in the United States, Europe, Asia and Australia, serves a set of clients across the world, including corporations, financial sponsors and government agencies. The Company provides financial professionals with an integrated platform that enables them to deliver advice to its clients. The Company also offers intellectual property advisory services..






