Houlihan Lokey, Inc. Class A (NYSE:HLI) Experiences Heavy Trading Volume 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsHoulihan Lokey, Inc. Class A (NYSE:HLI) Experiences Heavy Trading Volume
July 10, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



206K shares changed hands in the last trading session.  Trading volume was up 52.85% over the stocks average daily volume. 
 Here is the rundown on market activity for Houlihan Lokey, Inc. Class A (NYSE:HLI).   Irwin Gold, EXECUTIVE CHAIRMAN disclosed the sale of 15,743 shares of HLI stock. The shares were purchased at an average price of $29.05. The EXECUTIVE CHAIRMAN now owns $0 of the stock according to the SEC filing. CO-PRESIDENT Scott Joseph Adelson let go of 10,348 shares at an average price of $29.05 on Wed the 15th. The CO-PRESIDENT now owns $0 of the stock as reported to the SEC.
 David A. Preiser, CO-PRESIDENT sold $194,955 worth of shares at an average price of $29.05 on Wed the 15th. That brings the CO-PRESIDENT’s holdings to $0 per an SEC filing yesterday.
 Here are a few other firms who have also updated their positions.   As of quarter end Mackenzie Financial Corp had sold 12,300 shares trimming its stake by 54.2%. The value of the total investment in Houlihan Lokey, Inc. Class A decreased from $706,000 to $358,000 a change of 49.3% quarter to quarter. Morgan Stanley cut its ownership by selling 1,212 shares a decrease of 80.2%. Morgan Stanley controls 300 shares worth $10,000. The value of the position overall is down by 78.7%.
 As of the end of the quarter Tower Research Capital LLC (trc) had acquired  a total of 1,645 shares growing its position 579.2%. The value of the investment in Houlihan Lokey, Inc. Class A went from $6,000 to $66,000 increasing 1,000.0% since the last quarter. As of quarter end Goldman Sachs Group Inc had acquired 60,879 shares growing its holdings by 402.6%. The value of the investment in HLI went from $471,000 to $2,618,000 a change of $2,147,000 for the reporting period.        Advertisement






  On August 18 the stock rating was downgraded to “Hold” from “Buy” in a report from Sandler O'Neill. On September 8, 2015 Sandler O’Neill starting coverage on the stock by announcing an initial rating of “Buy” and price target of $25.00.
 On September 8 analysts at Goldman Sachs started covering the stock setting a rating of “Neutral” and projecting a price target of $25.00.
 The company is trading up by 1.04 percent from yesterday’s close.  Houlihan Lokey, Inc. Class A also announced a dividend for shareholders that was paid on Thursday June 15th, 2017.  The dividend was $0.200 per share for the quarter or $0.80 annualized.  This dividend amount was represent a yeild of $2.23.  The ex-dividend date was set for Wednesday the 31st of May 2017. 
 Shares of the company are trading at $35.94 which is marginally higher than $34.24, the stock’s 50 day moving average and which is just a bit higher than the 200 day moving average of $32.72.  The 50 day moving average was up $1.70 or +4.97% whereas the 200 day moving average was up $3.22 or +9.83%. 
 The company’s P/E ratio is 22.05 and the market cap of the company is 2.41B.  In the last earnings report the EPS was $1.63 and is estimated to be $1.94 for the current year with 67,128,000 shares outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is forecasted to be $0.40 with next year’s EPS projected to be $2.08. 
 Houlihan Lokey, Inc., launched on June 1, 2015, is a global independent investment bank that focuses on mergers and acquisitions (M&A), financings, financial restructurings and financial advisory services. The Company operates through three segments: Corporate Finance, Financial Restructuring and Financial Advisory Services. The Company, through its offices in the United States, Europe, Asia and Australia, serves a set of clients across the world, including corporations, financial sponsors and government agencies. The Company provides financial professionals with an integrated platform that enables them to deliver advice to its clients. The Company also offers intellectual property advisory services..
